description:
Singing is one of the most genuine and profound ways of worshiping God, and it has been part of the essence of Christian people since biblical times. Music connects us with our Creator and drives us to recognize the greatness and glory of the Lord.

Since its beginning, the Adventist Church has dedicated special attention and commitment to singing, forming a major part of the identity of its members.

Embark on a captivating journey through the rich history of the global Adventist movement with Jonathan Burt and Jim Nix. "Lest We Forget" offers a chance to be deeply inspired and moved by the stories that have impacted souls around the world. Don't miss this extraordinary exploration of our past, igniting your inspiration along the way.

_____________________________________________

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing and hope in Jesus.

Want to learn more about the Seventh-day Adventist Church? 
Visit our website at: https://www.adventist.org/
